#: ../new/noammoweapon.rst:8
msgid ":captiontag:`NoAmmoWeapon`"
msgstr ""

#: ../new/noammoweapon.rst:10
msgid ""
"Units and structures usually always use the same weapon against the same "
"target. If the weapon is not charged because ammo is depleted, the unit "
"will wait for it to reload. It will not try the next available weapon "
"that might not even need ammunition."
msgstr ""

#: ../new/noammoweapon.rst:15
msgid ""
"This feature works like :tag:`OpenTransportWeapon` (which forces another "
"weapon on the condition that a unit is in an open-topped transport). It "
"can be used to make the unit or structure switch to a less powerful "
"weapon automatically and use it until ammo has been reloaded, or to "
"disable firing any weapon when set to a weapon that requires ammo."
msgstr ""

#: ../new/noammoweapon.rst:28
msgid ":tagdef:`[TechnoType]NoAmmoWeapon=integer`"
msgstr ""

#: ../new/noammoweapon.rst:22
msgid ""
"The weapon index to switch to when there is no ammo left. This will "
"override the normal weapon selection and only allow this weapon to be "
"selected. Valid values :value:`0` for the primary weapon and :value:`1` "
"for the secondary. Use :value:`-1` to not switch weapons. Defaults to "
":value:`-1`."
msgstr ""

#: ../new/noammoweapon.rst:27
msgid ""
"This tag cannot override the :tag:`DeployFireWeapon` enabled by "
":tag:`DeployFire=yes` on :type:`VehicleTypes` and :tag:`InfantryTypes`."
msgstr ""

#: ../new/noammoweapon.rst:32
msgid ":tagdef:`[TechnoType]NoAmmoAmount=integer`"
msgstr ""

#: ../new/noammoweapon.rst:31
msgid ""
"If the current ammo is equal to or below this value, the "
":tag:`NoAmmoWeapon` will be used. Defaults to :value:`0`."
msgstr ""

